    "SCMs and their effect on hydration of cement-based materialsThe primary oxides found in ordinary Portland cement (OPC) phases are also present in (SCMs).",
    "Several factors, such as particle size distribution (PSD), chemical composition, surface area, and fineness, play a critical role in influencing the pozzolanic activity of SCMs.",
    "Among these, fineness is particularly important, as finer SCMs possess larger surface areas, which significantly enhance their reactivity.",
    "From a chemical perspective, the pozzolanic reaction of SCMs produces hydration products similar to those formed in OPC, although this reaction relies on the availability of calcium hydroxide (Ca(OH) 2) [26].",
    "Building on this understanding, previous studies have confirmed the role of SCMs in the hydration of cement-based materials and their contribution to pozzolanic activity."
  ],
